Added Object Lock: a reference-counted, attributable, time-bounded protection that prevents accidental deletion or modification of existing objects through the UI, REST API, and Jobs, with whole-object or field-level scope. Enforcement is global (a lock on any object is honored); Web UI and GraphQL lock state are available for every model, while the REST lock/release actions and lock-state fields are wired on Manufacturer as the reference integration in this release. Upgrade impact: because enforcement is global and on by default, once any object is locked, attempts to delete or update it through the UI, REST API, or Jobs return HTTP 409 (`ObjectLockedError`) until the lock is released — review existing automation before adopting locks.
